                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-291-victim2407 t18320906-291-viclabel1644"></join>. On the 20th of August the prisoner was with me the whole day, employed as <rs id="t18320906-291-deflabel1645" type="occupation">errand-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-291-defend2405 t18320906-291-deflabel1645"></join> - he had been employed four days; I missed him out of the shop for some time - I went out to inquire of a man selling fruit, and in consequence of what he said, I went and looked at the stock, and missed four pairs of boys' shoes; I went after him, and found him coming home - I taxed him with it, and he denied it; I called in a Policeman who found 1s. 6d. on him, and then he owned he had pawned them.</p>
